#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-composition-patterns/rules/patterns-children-over-render-props.md savings=-12%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Prefer Composing Children Over Render Props
M||impa|md
M||impa|cleaner composition, better readability
M||tags|composition, children, render-props
M||tx|---
M|Pref|tx|Use `children` for composition instead of `renderX` props. Children are more
M|Pref|tx|readable, compose naturally, and don't require understanding callback
M|Pref|tx|signatures.
M|Pref|**In|**
M|Pref|tx|```tsx
M|Pref|tx|fn Composer({
M|Pref|tx|renderHeader,
M|Pref|tx|renderFooter,
M|Pref|tx|renderActions,
M|Pref|}|{
M|Pref|rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|Pref|rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|Pref|rend|() => rc.ReactNode
M|Pref|tx|}) {
M|Pref|tx|return (
M|Pref|tx|<form>
M|Pref|tx|{renderHeader?.()}
M|Pref|tx|<Input />
M|Pref|{ren|<DefaultFooter />}
M|Pref|tx|{renderActions?.()}
M|Pref|tx|</form>
M|Pref|tx|)
M|Pref|tx|}
M|Pref|tx|// Usage is awkward and inflexible
M|Pref|tx|return (
M|Pref|tx|<Composer
M|Pref|tx|renderHeader={() => <CustomHeader />}
M|Pref|tx|renderFooter={() => (
M|Pref|tx|<>
M|Pref|tx|<Formatting />
M|Pref|tx|<Emojis />
M|Pref|tx|</>
M|Pref|tx|)}
M|Pref|tx|renderActions={() => <SubmitButton />}
M|Pref|tx|/>
M|Pref|tx|)
M|Pref|tx|```
M|Pref|**Co|**
M|Pref|tx|```tsx
M|Pref|func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|Pref|tx|return <form>{children}</form>
M|Pref|tx|}
M|Pref|func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|Pref|tx|return <footer className='flex'>{children}</footer>
M|Pref|tx|}
M|Pref|tx|// Usage is flexible
M|Pref|tx|return (
M|Pref|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Pref|tx|<CustomHeader />
M|Pref|tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Pref|tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|Pref|tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|Pref|tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|Pref|tx|<SubmitButton />
M|Pref|tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|Pref|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Pref|tx|)
M|Pref|tx|```
M|Pref|**Wh|**
M|Pref|tx|```tsx
M|Pref|tx|// Render props work well when you need to pass data back
M|Pref|tx|<List
M|Pref|tx|data={items}
M|Pref|tx|renderItem={({ item, index }) => <Item item={item} index={index} />}
M|Pref|tx|/>
M|Pref|tx|```
M|Pref|tx|Use render props when the parent needs to provide data or state to the child.
M|Pref|tx|Use children when composing static structure.